      <div xml:id="NA327-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">itu varaiyātu neṭuṅ kālam vantoḻuka āṟṟāḷāya talaimakaḷ vaṉpoṟai (ER, EV: vaṉpuṟai) yetiraḻintatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">This is how SHE who was unable to bear it when [HE] was coming for a long time without marrying was desolate in the face of encouragement.</p>
        </div>
      <div xml:id="NA327">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            nāṭal cāṉṟōr namputal paḻiyeṉiṟ</l>
<l>            pāṭila kaliḻuṅ kaṇṇoṭu cāayc</l>
<l>            cātalu miṉitē kātalan tōḻi</l>
<l>            yannilai yalla vāyiṉuñ cāṉṟōr</l>
<l>            kaṭaṉilai kuṉṟalu milareṉ ṟuṭaṉamarn</l>
<l>            tulakaṅ kūṟuva tuṇṭeṉa nilaiiya</l>
<l>            tāya mākalu murittē pōtaviḻ</l>
<l>            puṉṉai yōṅkiya kāṉaṟ</l>
<l>            ṟaṇṇan tuṟaivaṉ cāyaṉ mārpē.</l>
            </lg>
        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l rend="indent">If they say [it is] blame to trust in the noble one searching [me],</l>
<l rend="indent2">exhausted, with eyes that weep without sleeping,</l>
<l>dying [is] sweet, loving friend.</l>
<l>Even if those states are not so,</l>
<l rend="indent">since it is the talk of the world, staying together</l>
<l rend="indent">saying</l>
<l rend="indent4">“noble ones do not at all shrink from a state of duty(?),”</l>
<l>it is suitable that [I] possess permanently</l>
<l rend="indent">the graceful chest of the man from the cool ghat</l>
<l rend="indent2">by the seashore grove where the Puṉṉai trees have grown high,</l>
<l rend="indent4">buds opening.</l>
        </lg>
      </div>
